node.text:
I think it’s about time I address the “elephant in the room”…. I’ve been trying to avoid this topic for many months now because I’m very sensitive to it and just wasn’t quite ready to discuss anything on here about it. But I have been getting an overwhelming number of messages asking me about Bella’s eyes… so I guess it’s time for me to share… 
Yes she has strabismus.
She is being seen by the BEST doctors in the country, and rest assured we are doing everything we can to get her eyes corrected.
Many of you messaged me saying your kids had the same issue and after corrective surgery it fixed everything perfectly. 🙌🏻 
Praying for the same results of course 🤞🏻
If you have any advice or positive stories you can share about this, please let me know. Anything will help. 🙏🏻
Thank you all for your encouraging messages and support. You guys are amazing 🥰
#strabismus #wonderingeye #babygirl #eyesurgery #babyeyesurgery #kidseyesurgery #strabismussurgery #supportmoms #momofthreekids

node.text:
And that’s it! You’re 1 already. 😭😭😭😭
Bella barely made a dent in that cake. She likes chewing on the flowers much more 🌸😂 I’ll have to make a comparison post with Lia, Maya and Bella on their cake smash shoot… it’s fun to look at but what you can really see in them, is their individual character and personality. 

Lia dived right into her cake and was literally covered from head to toe in it. She took over on that shoot and was the center of attention. She made sure to be! She completely destroyed the cake, danced, laughed, and couldn’t get enough of it. That pretty much sums her up… she always has to be in control, she’s a leader, very dominant and has to be first no matter what. Lia is my social butterfly and has to be the center of attention. 

Maya was very careful and didn’t really want to touch it… she analyzed it carefully and after a few pushes to get her to stick her hand into it, she finally just “accidentally” fell into it but didn’t enjoy it much at all. She didn’t enjoy the mess. Maya is very organized and loves everything to be in its place. She always thinks before saying something and is always very careful with her actions. She is also extremely caring and always puts her sisters first…

Bella… well, I still need some time to let her personality develop but she was not into that cake what so ever. She didn’t even want to explore it. Not even after I made her touch it a bit, she looked at her cake filled hand in disgust and wiped it on her dress to get it all off. So we shall see how she turns out. 🤷🏻‍♀️

Did you have cake smash shoots with your kids? Tell me about them please!! 👇🏻👇🏻
